TSS is a cryptographic primitive for distributed key generation and signing. You can think about it as a better version of multisig. The main difference is that multisig is usually implemented on the application layer of the blockchain, for example, as a smart contract on Ethereum, whereas TSS support is always possible regardless of the blockchain, as it relies on basic cryptographic elements.
